fields.name: iTOW
fields.description:
GPS time of week of the navigation epoch.
See section iTOW timestamps in the integration manual for details.

fields.name: gnssId
fields.description: GNSS identifier (see Satellite Numbering) for assignment

fields.name: svId
fields.description: Satellite identifier (see Satellite Numbering) for assignment

fields.name: elev
fields.description: Elevation (range: +/-90), unknown if out of range

fields.name: azim
fields.description: Azimuth (range 0-360), unknown if elevation is out of range

bits.name: qualityInd
bits.description:
Signal quality indicator:
• 0 = no signal
• 1 = searching signal
• 2 = signal acquired
• 3 = signal detected but unusable
• 4 = code locked and time synchronized
• 5, 6, 7 = code and carrier locked and time synchronized

bits.name: svUsed
bits.description: 1 = Signal in the subset specified in Signal Identifiers is currently being used for navigation

bits.name: health
bits.description:
Signal health flag:
• 0 = unknown
• 1 = healthy
• 2 = unhealthy

bits.name: diffCorr
bits.description: 1 = differential correction data is available for this SV

bits.name: smoothed
bits.description: 1 = carrier smoothed pseudorange used

bits.name: orbitSource
bits.description:
Orbit source:
• 0 = no orbit information is available for this SV
• 1 = ephemeris is used
• 2 = almanac is used
• 3 = AssistNow Offline orbit is used
• 4 = AssistNow Autonomous orbit is used
• 5, 6, 7 = other orbit information is used

bits.name: ephAvail
bits.description: 1 = ephemeris is available for this SV

bits.name: almAvail
bits.description: 1 = almanac is available for this SV

bits.name: anoAvail
bits.description: 1 = AssistNow Offline data is available for this SV

bits.name: aopAvail
bits.description: 1 = AssistNow Autonomous data is available for this SV

bits.name: reserved_bit_15
bits.description: Reserved

bits.name: sbasCorrUsed
